==Korean==
===Noun===
'''알까기''' (''alkkagi'') (''cf. Greek [[αρχή]] (archê) "beginning, origin"'')
# [[hatching]], [[incubation]] (''from Latin [[incubare]] "to lie on" (eggs, etc.)'')   

====Synonyms====
*[[부화]] ([[孵化]], ''buhwa'') [[hatching]], [[incubation]] 
*[[난생]] ([[卵生]], ''nansaeng'') [[oviparity]], [[oviparous]] [[birth]]

====Antonyms====
*[[태생]] ([[胎生]], ''taesaeng'') [[viviparity]], [[viviparous]] [[birth]]

====Related terms====
*[[알]] (''al, ar'') [[egg]]
*[[낳다]] (''nahda'') To [[breed]], [[lay]] (''eggs'')
*[[품다]] (''pumda'') To [[embrace]], [[incubate]] 
*[[까다]] (''kkada'') To [[shell]], [[castrate]], [[hatch]] 
*[[깨다]] (''kkaeda'') To [[break]], [[crack]], [[awake]], [[hatch]]

====See also====
*[[난생신화]] ([[卵生神話]], ''nansaeng-sinhwa'') [[oviparous]] [[myth]] (''such that the founder of a dynasty '''hatched out of an egg''', perhaps simply serving as a metaphor for the '''beginning''' of a new nation.'') 

